oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Photographic print of a group of Confederate veterans
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Large group of Confederate veterans posing in front of a clap board building. James Calvin Carnahan is the 8th from left on the back row. Davis Murray is the 7th from left seated. Cpl. James Calvin Carnahan, Co.G, 8th Tenn.(Smith's) Cav. Regt., CSA enlisted April 27, 1862. Murray was from the area between Murfreesboro and Bradyville in Rutherford County, Tenn. and is most likely Pvt. D.B. Murray, Co. B, 8th Tenn. (Smith's) Cav. Regt., CSA. His Father was Hiram Murray. Photographer was H.O. Todd.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Carnahan, James Calvin; Murray, Davis
